openhmd
------------------------------------------
OpenHMD aims to provide a Free and Open Source API and drivers for immersive
technology, such as head mounted displays with built in head tracking.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.7-1
  libGL1-18.0.5-1
  libGLEW2.1-2.1.0-1
  libhidapi-devel-0.8.0-rc1-1
  libhidapi0-0.8.0-rc1-1
  libopenhmd-devel-0.3.0-1bl1
  libopenhmd0-0.3.0-1bl1
  libSDL2_2.0_0-2.0.7-1
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.14.5-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-7
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.openhmd.net/

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/OpenHMD/OpenHMD/archive/0.3.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack openhmd-0.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./openhmd-0.3.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/openhmd-0.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/openhmd-0.3.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libopenhmd0-0.3.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libopenhmd-devel-0.3.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(openhmd)
  /usr/bin/openhmd-openglexample.exe
  /usr/bin/openhmd-simple.exe
  /usr/bin/openhmd-unittests.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/openhmd.README
  /usr/share/doc/openhmd/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/openhmd/README.md

(libopenhmd0)
  /usr/bin/cygopenhmd-0.dll

(libopenhmd-devel)
  /usr/include/openhmd/openhmd.h
  /usr/lib/libopenhmd.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/openhmd.pc

